        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/27837",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=beberlei",
                        "name": "beberlei",
                        "displayName": "Benjamin Eberlei",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This is possible any may be even included for the next minor version 1.8 in february.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=beberlei",
                        "name": "beberlei",
                        "displayName": "Benjamin Eberlei",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-01-07T04:03:57.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-01-07T04:03:57.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/27846",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=beberlei",
                        "name": "beberlei",
                        "displayName": "Benjamin Eberlei",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "It seems that i am very forgetful. This functionality is already included through the following method\n\n{code}\n$view->jQuery()->addStylesheet()\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=beberlei",
                        "name": "beberlei",
                        "displayName": "Benjamin Eberlei",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-01-07T14:31:10.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-01-07T14:31:10.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/27860",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=laurent+melmoux",
                        "name": "laurent melmoux",
                        "displayName": "Laurent Melmoux",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "**jQuery()->addStylesheet()** will include a css file regardless if ui is enable or not. \nWhat I'm proposing is a method to setup the css theme and this one would be included with <?= $view->jQuery() ?> only if  ui is enable. Even better, it should be included only if we are using any widget.\nWhat do you think ?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=laurent+melmoux",
                        "name": "laurent melmoux",
                        "displayName": "Laurent Melmoux",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-01-07T23:34:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-01-07T23:34:29.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/27861",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=beberlei",
                        "name": "beberlei",
                        "displayName": "Benjamin Eberlei",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Ah ok i understand your issue :-)\n\nThere is currently no detection mechanism wheater a widget was loaded or not. What i propose you could use in your case, in the layout do:\n\n{code}\n<?php if($this->jQuery()->uiIsEnabled()): ?>\n<link ...>\n<?php endif; ?>\n{code}\n\nI dont know if yet another method in the container is a good idea, since there is already this solution to the problem.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=beberlei",
                        "name": "beberlei",
                        "displayName": "Benjamin Eberlei",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-01-08T01:47:44.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-01-08T01:47:44.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28093",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=laurent+melmoux",
                        "name": "laurent melmoux",
                        "displayName": "Laurent Melmoux",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I did not think about this trick,  thanks :).  \nIMHO, an other method would make it a bit more elegant, as all the setup could be centralized in the bootstrap. But  this probably  need a bit more thinking to fit in a bigger picture with theme and widget. ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=laurent+melmoux",
                        "name": "laurent melmoux",
                        "displayName": "Laurent Melmoux",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-01-12T00:43:13.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-01-12T00:43:13.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28567",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sico",
                        "name": "sico",
                        "displayName": "Simon Corless",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I agree I think this would be a good idea, or to set the base path for the skin\n$this->jQuery()->setUiLocalPathTheme('ui\/themes\/mytheme\/')\n\nThen each element would require it's own stylesheet, the skins seem pretty robust now so it wouldn't be too hard to automatically call the specific stylesheets and it would make setup much easier!",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sico",
                        "name": "sico",
                        "displayName": "Simon Corless",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-02-01T12:36:59.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-02-01T12:36:59.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
